content.detailedDescription: On sat sept 26th 2015 at aprx 918pm az time. myself and a friend were sitting outside and we both saw, a box shape, with 4 glowing lights on it appear in the south east sky it did not come up from the ground, but just came from out of nowhere, went up for a few sec, then moved left to the east and then just disappeared in the sky. it was only there for about 8-10 sec, could not get a picture, almost seemed to grow in size slightly as it moved left before it was gone.  it almost looked like it was on fire but it was the lights. nothing else to report on it.
content.summary: 4 lights in the sky- excitement in the sky - se phoenix

content.detailedDescription:
It was daybreak in autumn. i saw a very bright "spotlight" facing the bus. we passed the field where i saw the light. approximately a mile further up the road the craft was hovering over the tree line and over half of the two lane road. after i observed for a few seconds then the craft slowly "eased" back over the forest. i perceived a sensation that the craft wanted me to see it.

i felt a little upset for most of the day, and also felt as if a "curtain of unseen reality" had been opened to give me a peek. i had never been a believer in et craft before this.
content.summary: I witnessed the craft at two locations from a schoolbus witness.

content.detailedDescription: I was walking around the heinz factory from the canteen to the stores. i looked up at an airliner that was flying past and noticed approx 5 shining objects flying high but leaving no vapor trail the objects where travelling slowly north three of them in a triangle formation. i phoned a friend to come out of the factory and see if he could identify them. the time stamp on my phone was 11:15. neither my friend or i could identify them hence this report.
content.summary: 5 shiny metallic objects flying north in triangle formation. also 2 airliners in sky at same time

content.detailedDescription: Witness (a) and (b) have observed a bright star-like object to the east nightly during the early morning hours between 5am to 6:30 am, 11sep to 26sep2015.  the observed inclination angle is between 15 to 20 degrees.  when viewed with binoculars a colorful light show is observed within the object itself.
content.summary: Bright star tree-top level, with binoculars bunch of colored lights within it, happens nightly about 5 to 6:30am.

content.detailedDescription: When i was about to enter my home from getting some dinner, i noticed a slow moving diamond shaped object, with a space between the ends of the bottom of the triangular part of the diamond, the object had two smaller exterior lights, and one larger white middle one, moving easterly. i lost sight when it exited my peripheral vision. i had no feelings, but i was some what surprised and wondered.
content.summary: About to walk in home, saw slow moving object, moved out of vision.

content.detailedDescription: I was out riding my bike going west on curry from 68th st towards mill ave.  i decided to take a picture of the tempe town lake with the lights and buildings in the background.  i took a few pictures of the surrounding area and went on my way.  i edited some of the pictures but never used them for anything artistic and they have been on my harddrive eversince.  the other day, i was looking through a folder in my computer that i labeled "landscapes" and looked some other landscapes that i took photos of.  when i brought up this photo, i noticed some small white dots on the photo so i then zoomed in.  i thought, "wow", this has lights like ufo photos lol.  i really don't know what it is but it is very interesting.  there is an airport near by so maybe it's just something from there but i thought i would send it in anyway.  thanks
content.summary: I remember taking a picture and leaving, nothing unusual

content.detailedDescription: My friend and i were outside star gazing roughly around 11:07pm. we were sitting on the front porch and we noticed an object hovering in the sky that seemed to just appear out of nowhere. at first we assumed the object was a plane coming in with headlights on, but then we noticed it wasn't moving at all. then we became absolutely dumbfounded.  my friend and i watched the object for nearly three minutes without the object having any visible change. we continued to watch the object. around 11:10-11:11 the object began to pulse in the sky and two more lights lit up around the original light source. roughly twenty seconds later we observed at least three orbs come from the middle of the light source. the orbs flashed multiple colors and then just seemed to vanish almost like they were cloaked. the triangle shaped lights remained for roughly three and a half minutes and then they began to slowly dip downwards. they seemed to descend for two seconds before zipping straight upwards and seeming to completely vanish from sight. during the encounter i pulled my phone out and was going to try and take a video. unfortunately my battery had just up and died (i'm assuming the craft had something to do with it being there was a very high pitched noise along with a hum/buzz noise all through the air.) we observed the lights from what appeared to be a distance of maybe 2.75 miles away at a 40ish degree angle in the sky. during the encounter my friend and i both seemed to just be speechless and really couldn't talk. we seemed to be absolutely dumbfounded and had no words to say besides "do you see that too?"
content.summary: Triangle craft that hovered, pulsed, let out orbs of light, then zipped into the sky.

content.detailedDescription: First was riding in car westbound on goodman rd. saw the 2 strange lights (red/orange kind of flashing) behaving unlike typical aircraft, more like parts of one massive craft. they remained equidistant (from each other) although sometimes one or both would disappear above cloud cover.On return trip east bound,  they were still hovering together, we pulled into a parking lot (cousin went inside to buy beer) lights went south then stopped moving/changed direction again (was observing them from stationary position in parking lot at that time ). they remained equidistant, reminding me of the 'black triangle' i saw years back,  but if that's what this was,  it kept one corner above cloud cover the entire time i observed.  we then headed east  where i lost sight of it/them. the lights remained localised to one area, as if they were doing aerial reconnaissance  (like search helicopters,  but silent, and only one big light per 'object' instead of the several lights typical of normal aircraft. i  would say they were planets,  if  stars would have been visible and they didn't move so intelligently. would have taken a photo but niece was playing minecraft on my phone.  plus i would have needed optical zoom to get anything decent.  my cousin said airplanes would not change direction like that. can't judge distance without knowing exact size,  but i know where we drove and we drove on east and west of it, and right 'under', so i have a pretty decent estimation of what it was over.  it kind of circled the area, but so slowly i can't say definite flight pattern.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Other
content.summary: 2 red/orange lights remained equidistant, hovering over area, changing direction,  staying in/around clouds

content.detailedDescription: I was at home and went out on my patio to look at the moon because of the up coming blood moon tomorrow night...The sky was clear as can and no clouds at all...I could see the stars then a lot lower was a star like light...I though it might be an airplane light but it was not blinking colors...It was moving from right to left not really fast but not that slow either....All of sudden another light appeared right in front like it split into two they kept moving for a couple seconds then it went back into the one light and after a couple seconds completely dissapered...I was shocked and ran inside to tell my mom...She said she believed me but i really don't think so because we were just talking about ufo's the last couple days...I went back out to look and saw a shooting star but this was nothing like what i just saw...
content.summary: Star like light turned into two then back to one then disappeared

content.detailedDescription: Family at camp in potter count pa, sitting outside on back deck between 9pm and 10pm on august 15th with my mother..I remember due to my birthday being the 13th. we observed an orange round glow on the right above the mountain rim, it moved slowly towards us, no sound was ever noticed, we talked a few minutes, looked again and it was high above the tree to the right of our cabin, hovering. no pulsating, no sound, bright, solid orange. we watched it make a slow path back to the rim of the mountain and back to the tree a few times. at this point i called for my dad and husband, neither came out, again the object moved to the tree as previously done, however it shifted course dramatically and very, very fast and i went out front to find it with no luck. i rejoined my mom on the back deck, at this point we noticed searchlights all over the sky, clouds had begun to move in by then so the searchlights were easy to see due to the reflection, finally my mother said this is very odd, i don't know what that was, and went in the cabin, the searchlights continued for about 10 minutes. we both strained to hear any sounds, initially we thought of a helicopter, but the behavior and the lack of sound voided that theory. this has been bothering me for a while now, the fact that my mom agreed something was odd struck me, for my peace of mind i needed to get other opinions and share this incident, if there is a qualifying answer to what we witnessed i am all ears. i do regret that i did not have a camera with the capacity to take night pictures. i have tried all i can think of to disprove this but i am stumped. from some crazy fireworks, to a meteor, it just does not fit into anything we have seen in our known skies.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Orange round object moved slowly circling mtn top to tree point off back but higher multiple times, slow then fast, searchlights began after it left.

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside at a cook-out (very sober) and enjoying the super moon.  an orange object appeared in the se sky.  first thought it was a "fire lantern" ascending.  i don't think "fire lanterns" are a common event in west virginia.  

soon realized the object was tracking straight line from se to nw (not the prevailing wind direction) as it passed over the clouds above.   the object's altitude was 10,000-15,000 feet, speed 300-500mph.  object passed over the clouds and emerged on the other side.  i did see commercial airline traffic (with strobe lights) in the vicinity at around 30,000 ft.  lost sight of the object over the horizon.  about 5 minutes later a second object appeared, it was similar in appearance, speed, direction, and altitude.  the orange "fire" effect on both objects was the same as it approached and departed.
content.summary: Orange high speed fire lantern like objects

content.detailedDescription: My son and i were driving on the freeways and saw three bright orange colored lights, looked like they were on fire. they flew in uniform the entire time. was not a plane or aircraft.  moving very slow.  i felted somewhat freaked out because i do not believe in ufo or whatever, however there is no valid explanation for what my son and i saw tonight!!!! wow
content.summary: Three brights lights in sky looked like they were on fire, 210 & cherry fontana ca

content.detailedDescription: My family and i were driving home from eating dinner on rt 44 in seekonk ma. i was driving and my 16 year old daughter was the first to witness the object. she asked me what it was and i first thought it was a helicopter. it was to my left so i slowed down and knew very quickly it was not a helicopter. my wife and oldest daughter all saw the same thing. a black triangular shaped object hovering and moving unlike any  aircraft i have ever seen. it has very bright lights on its undercarriage in each corner. when i pulled over to turn the vehicle around and get another look at it, the object was gone and there were no signs of it, or any lights in the distance.  we had the windows down and were close enough that it was odd because the object was silent. i was driving so i couldn't take a picture but to be honest we were all mesmerized by what we saw. my wife is the biggest skeptic and saw exactly what i saw. she thinks it was a drone. this was no drone. military craft maybe. extraterrestrial maybe. either way it was a black triangular shaped silent object with bright lights in each corner that hovered and moved unlike any aircraft that i have ever seen or heard of. i wish we were able to get a photograph of it.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change
content.summary: Black triangular shaped silent object with bright lights was hovering and moving before disappearing.

content.detailedDescription: Noticed immediately when i stepped outside my door. it was moving in a study horizontal line. the wobbling is due for me trying to get my iphone video camera ready. i am very bad about judging distance. there was no sound at all. it was large compared to other items in the sky. larger than a jet would be by far. i tried to follow it before it went behind the trees but i lost it so only the first few frames of the video have the actual object. i am not very good with enlarging or slowing things down but i did manage to isolate and zoom in on a couple of frames.  one looks like a detailed disc object with something perhaps protruding from each end and the faint outline of an inverted v in the middle.   the other photo looks like a blob, i don't know if my wobbling phone caused that, but it is very different color from the first photo.   these were both from the same object
content.summary: Vivid pulsating light

content.detailedDescription:
we were travelling south on i-95 from orono to bangor.  i saw the object come out over the trees up ahead on the right.  it was moving in a straight line at a slight angle to the freeway, maybe five miles an hour.  at first i doubted my eyes, and i said something to my wife, and pointed at it.

  i pulled over, and my wife and i both got out.  the object was completely silent as it slowly floated over the freeway.  other cars drove by, but not many (this is maine).  one of the cars pulled over and i am not positive, but it was two or three people got out, and like us, they were just staring at it.  eventually the object floated over the trees, and in a few moments was lost to sight, completely.

  we went on to bangor to shop, and when i got home i called my father (who had been in the air force during the cold war, and rarely spoke about what he did, but i know it involved analog computers, tracking the moon and sun and the north star, and high performance jet aircraft (f104 starfighter is the only one he would talk about).  i told him what i saw, and asked what he thought i should do.  my father said something that surprised me.

he said, "son, based on what i saw back in the day, this was a friendly.  i don't know why they truck them out, but they do it on purpose, and want to hear the civilian feedback.  keep this to yourself because if you talk about it, you might end up looking like a fool."

i regret that i did not make an effort to contact the folks on the other side of the freeway.  we really should have exchanged numbers or us mail addresses.
content.summary: Large metalic triangle floats over i-95 between orono and bangor

content.detailedDescription: In my bakyard. horizontal ascent with huge red-pink light. i first think it was a weather balloon ot a helicopter, but too fast !
content.summary: Horizontal ascent with huge red-pink light. then slow hovering with many accelerations. finally flashes off and rapid descent like a leaf

content.detailedDescription: I was taking pictures of what i belive was chem trails and later on in the day i was looking at the pics and saw a bright light in the pics, and the first pic i took has a blue smudge to the right of the bright light , and the second pic has no blue smudge. don't know if this is anything but take a look. i took a few pics but only two in that same direction.
content.summary: Saw a weird light in a couple photos i took

content.detailedDescription: My daughter christina blankenship text me at exactly 12:05 am. 9/26/15 and told me "u should go outside and take pics at the moon and see what turns out around it. looks like a giant giant ring around it". i went out almost immediately with my phone and turned on the video camera on it and zoomed in as far as it would go. while i was video taping it looked like a million gazillion little things flying around what appeared to be the moon going a million gazillion miles an hour. wow!! after i video taped a few minutes i went and got my daughter bobbi adams to come look. she also brought her daughter ahmya and one of my other granddaughters izailia with her. i also called my son uriah and wanted him to video zoomed in and in slow motion but he was in bed and really didnt want to get up. anyway, i have 2 videos on my phone then i didn't have anymore room left to record. you can hear me on the phone with him on the video. later on my daughter and 2 granddaughters went right down the street to the pitngo store. what appeared to be the moon still looking strange, i had my other camera with me and video taped again from the store parking lot. there was a giant giant shadow hovering around the supposed "moon" and moving all around it. my granddaughters were very scared especially izailia when she could also see the giant shadow actually moving around said "moon". i called izailia's mother and wanted her to video tape but she also was in bed and didn't want bothered. my daughter christina text me back at exactly 1:51 a.M. and said, "don't it look fkn weird? looks like a big ufo but using camo to reflect the moon so we still see it". i text a few times after that. at 1:52 a.M. i said that she should see my fkn video. at 1:58 a.M. i asked her if she been outside watching it. and asked if she seen the shadows moving around it. no reply. at 2:28 i asked her if she was still up? it's going on all night. no reply. at 3:44 i said, "no where in sight now, hmmmmm. no reply.  wow!!!! i wasn't feeling good in my head, izailia sick to her stomach. bobbi didn't really feel well. i felt so freaking weird like i couldn't concentrate.
content.summary: Appeared to be the moon but was swirling a million miles a minute.

content.detailedDescription: I was leaving my apartment to take my dog for a walk when i saw what looked like a a huge star in the sw sky. it was the only thing in the sky except for the moon. it was stationary for 10 minutes and then started moving slowly to the east as it started changing colors from silver to orange to red and it moved slowly eastward until i lost site of it.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Star like, then changing from silver to orange, to red.

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my phone and someone messaged saying that the moon looked beautiful tonight a it did. i the looked out the window to see 4 red lights in the sky. at first i thought it was glare coming from the window, then i opened my window to discover these orbs flying across the sky. i took a picture then called my mother. i habe never felt so nervous in my life.

when i was speaking to her she could see the orbs flying where i was i could see exactly where they were coming from. i seen 4 orbs form a diamond shape then orb into one then shoot across the sky one at a time. all in there were 7-8 orbs flying in the same flight path.
content.summary: Seen from my living room window red orb shooting out 8 red orbs across the sky

content.detailedDescription: Saw a bright white light moving in an upward direction then stopped and was motionless for around 30secs then moved to the right again in straight line then stopped and again motionless for around 30secs then double backed on its self to the same point again motionless for 30secs then moved in straight line left then stopped for motionless for around 30secs again then double backed on itself to the original point it was motionless for about a minute before slowly descending then changed from the bright white light to a pulsating red ball shaped sphere and moved in a fast erratic movement before disappearing into the woodland,i observed this from bedroom window which is facing a mountain which is approx 1mile away and i know the mountain is around 900feet and the object was just slightly above the mountain top and descended approx to 200/300 feet from the ground,it was a very warm misty summer night and visibility was not good,at 1st i thought it was a rescue/police helicopter but they would not fly so close to the electric pylons or change into a red pulsating sphere...There was a direction to the white light as if it was searching/scanning for something....Very strange.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: Observed white light moving in slow straight upward and sideways whilst hooverong before changing to a pulasting red light with eratic fast movement

content.detailedDescription:
Sept.25th 2015, anchorage ak while in my home at 20:45 that i have lived there for thirty years. my home, elevation 1000 feet. house located on three acres. two large windows in my living area,from sitting on my chair, i can see to my left through the  west window and in front of me the north window. while watching tv, i saw a very large "orange" light traveling west to east through the trees, approximate one mile out 2,000 feet elevation. i've seen hundreds of air craft (planes/helicopters) over the years(from my yard or through the house windows. i've seen bright white lights, green and red marker lights attach to them. this sighting in the corner of my left eye i could see the orange light out my left window traveling slow to the west.  it was large like a basketball size, not like small directional lights of aircraft. it came to view through my north window. my first thought was a meteorite passing,but,no tail? gosh that's slow,then i thought wtf is that! i ran to my west side exit door, to the front to my house onto the deck and watch the slow moving orange bright fuzzy basketball size light traveling slow.
the trees in the area were at times blocking my view. i thought to myself, to slow for a aircraft, no noise of rotor blades of a helicopter. this event lasted for ninety seconds to one hundred. i thought about calling the locate police dispatch office to see if any one call in but decide it was a non emergency. i violated that call. it went out of sight due to the tress and the low elevation with it having a slight decent to it. it's speed could be around 50 mph. i'm sixty years of age. afterwards i thought to myself "that's the first". the following day, i search the on line and noted very similar sightings on your sight in my area of fifty miles range.
content.summary: Large orange orb/light travling west toeast

content.detailedDescription:
My fiancé and i were driving on interstate 40-e in between the cities of mt. juliet and lebanon, tn. we noticed about 1/2 a mile ahead of us that one particular section of clouds was glowing a bright red color. the weather conditions were rainy, thick cloud cover, no visible moon or stars. we briefly went through the options of what could be making the cloud glow that color (the moon, a light from the ground, etc.) the cloud was directly above the middle of the interstate, so we ruled out the option of a light on the ground causing the glow. the sun had been set for over an hour, so we ruled out that option as well. the moon was not in a current postion to cause the glow in that area. 
i pulled out my phone, since neither of us had ever seen something like this before. i snapped a few pictures and we then drove directly underneath the cloud and still it glowed a very unnatural red. the cloud hung fairly low, seemingly lower than the clouds surrounding it. we live in lebanon, so once we got home we continued to discuss what we saw. while looking at the pictures i captured of the cloud, we notice that there were visible red lights in the sky above the cloud in the picture. unfortunately, my phone camera did not capture the red coloration that the cloud was in person, but instead looks more yellow/orange in the photograph. however, the lights captured are indeed red. so, if i did capture a  craft or whatever the red lights are, it would confirm the cause of the glowing red cloud below.

i am hoping you all can analyze my picture to rule out if the lights i captured were reflections from something on the highway or if the glowing cloud could have a natural, scientific explanation. a few weeks ago, we also witnessed a flying object with red lights across the street from our house in lebanon, which flew in a very unnatural manner- going directly up, down and side to side. also, disappearing and reappearing again. we took a video of the object, but the quality isn't the best. we have both seen drones before, and did not feel like the object was a drone (of course, we could be wrong). my fiancé also heard a very strange, loud humming noise late at night while sitting outside our home last week (he described it as sounding just like a spacecraft from something out of a movie), so we are starting to get a little weirded out by all of this happening so close to our home within the past month!
content.summary: Singular cloud (low hanging) glowing bright red apart from all other clouds.

content.detailedDescription: Test
content.summary: Test

content.detailedDescription: It was 9-23 2015  i was stanging in frount o the savealot  in danville il beteew 745 to 8 pm  looking out to the south west i saw a very bright fuszy redorange moveing  from the south  west to the north east  it was mabey 10d above  the hovezon  was as bright as a stop light  light moveing very slowly  at times it seen to all most hover in the sky  and i  did not hear any noise nor see any blinking light  like a plane wood have nor was  it a blimp    then   it slowly turn to the west and then the light on it blinked  out and i never saw it after that vi never seen a  light in the sky  that bright and  big
content.summary: Just a very stang fussy red orange light moveing very very slowly  in the sky

content.detailedDescription: I was on my backdoor stoop giving my 2 dogs toilet break. the dogs were barking so loudly i tried to see them, it was nighttime. that is when i noticed the object. it at first appeared to be a whitish disc that suddenly moved backwards from it's apparent flight path at that moment it suddenly moved forward a full length ahead of where it was originally. that is when i noticed while it slowed down considerably it had rotating lights along its entire shape red white some yellow with a bluish constant light behind the other rotating lights.I watched it until it disappeared behind the tree line. it was a very clear beautiful night.This was my second visual sighting of an unknown objest. the last time i was with my parents on the side porch. i was 7yrs old so when my dad said too look i did. he said those were not airplane colors. this current sighting was fascinating. i felt wide awake and concerned. i was not drinking or taking any illegal substances. i was clear minded. after i told my wife what i saw (she was at work) she has been uncompfortable ever since.This is the first time i felt a strong need to report something like this. i knew it was not an airplane or helicopter.
content.summary: Clear night, object moved backwards then slowly moved east all in the the same flight line.

content.detailedDescription:
just a couple minutes before 8pm on the evening of sept 24/15 i went outside to my backyard with my dog to have a cigarette. i walked up to the hill ( 4 steps off the deck ) and i looked up to the sky ( the sky was that blue night sky not dark black) i see this huge what appeared like a star but was massive and so close. i knew 100% this isnt right and just then all these pink tesla ball tentacles started coming off of this " star " looking thing and within a second - it seemed as if this " star " turned inside out of itself and i could see orange and blue lights merged together and wham! i see this dark shape with lights ( not blinking ) coming towards my house. i never once took my eyes off of it and as it went over my house i could see the bottom and full shape of the object. it was in the shape of a row boat /bullet. it 100% had no wings or tail. the lower bottom had two lights that were peach orange and in the shape of those cement park barriers that lay on the ground in a parking space - they were vertigo - one on far left and other on far right. above these two lights was a large circular ball light of blue. none of these lights blinked at all and stayed on. the craft gave off a sound that i unfortunately can not describe because i have never heard a sound like that to compare. i thought there was something wrong with it mechanically because of sound but perhaps that is the way it sounds normally..I really don't know.
it was the size of a large building and moved slow but steady over the house.

when the object went over me i could feel a numb sorta tingly feeling within both arms, neck and my head. what i found strange is that i knew it was a ufo but i just all calm like walked back into my house looking at my arms and thinking " they are real " i felt this sensation for 1hr and 9mins.

also when i came in the house i looked at the time and no more then 2 mins had passed. i drew the craft and wrote some details within a minute of being in the house.
 
i have been feeling since that night what must be post traumatic stress.
content.summary: Row boat shape ( sorta like a bullet but more like a row boat. had 3 lights.

content.detailedDescription: It was the evening of july 4th 1977 just after the sun went down past the horizon. a group of 5 of us in a small town in montana. my sister, three cousins & me were in the center of the street outside where i used to live. when we noticed a sphere start to rise up from the horizon in the south. it's been over 38 years from now, so exactly what all colors it changed isn't completely clear to me, but i remember it had to have been a shere for the reason the colors it chose to be was a lighter tint in the center and much darker tint around the edge. it had to have been enormous for the reason what ever color it chose to be made the entire predawn sky a lighter,  even tint the same color it was. while it was rising, it changed just about every color one could think of from the time it started from the southern horizon until the time it went down beyond the northern horizon. it was perfectly centered in the sky, moving at a consistant slow speed. because it changed the color of the entired predawn sky the color it chose to be, i was thinking many people had to have seen this. but also it seemed as if it was ment for us.. or even me, for the reason when it left the sky, over the northern horizon, it left the predawn sky the same color it was the last moment i saw it. then the sky seemed like it took some time as it faided into darkness as it was night. continuing to keep that last color. as it was happening, i remember asking the group i was with as they were staring at it with dropped jaws, if they saw this object in the sky. they didn't respond. so i asked them again if they saw what was happening. in a dase, as they all were, my cousin brad responed, yaa... then i said, i will never forget this for the rest of my life. after the incident, nothing was said about it. i think we all just forgot about it. a few years past, and i remembered it again. i didn't understand why it was forgotten. so i started to ask my sister and cousins if they remembered it happening. none of my cousins remembered it but my sister said she did, vagly remember something. i did from time to time tell the story to people. but i never did report it until now. for the reason, there was no one or no where to report somethng like this that i knew of. i believe it really did happen for the reason i've never heard of anything like this before and have never saw anything like it on tv or any videos. how could i have just made something like this up. i want to know more about it if possible. i would even consider being hipnotized if it brings me closer to an understanding.
content.summary: Large colorful spere moving consistant one direction

content.detailedDescription: I was jogging in morning, pitch black out.  very familiar with stars and venus seen to the east.  i notice the object on one of my laps.  it was extremely bright.  i knew it wasn't there on my prior lap, it was much brighter than venus which is usually the brightest thing in the sky at that hour.  venus was simultaneously visible.  the object moved slowly from north to south and disappeared behind the treeline.  i took photos with iphone  no sound.  it became more dim towards the end of the sighting and i noticed blinking lights more similar to an airplane, but i have never seen an airplane so bright.  there is a small airport to the south so we see airplanes frequently, day and night.  this was very unusual for an airplane.  the photos reveal details i could not appreciate with naked eye.  seems to have three lights and possible dome shape.  the object appeared simply as a bright orange ball during these pictures.  the last photo with a small orange rectangle was taken when it became more dim at the end of sighting.  the structure on left is my neighbors house or a reflection of my barn from behind me?
content.summary: Brightest thing in sky, brighter than venus, traveled slow from north to south, became dimmer, disappeared behind treelike

content.altitude: 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (no cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription:
I was testing my new night scope i had built with video camara attached and recording, with soul purpose of captureing these events on camara , i had been out my back yard , filming for aprox 45 mins, when i noticed a bright object (orb) very close just off to my right aprox 200 meters away aprox 200 meter off the ground. i quickly got camara onto object and began recording when it almost instantly began to get brighter , i for a split second thought it was a helicopter spotlight shineing on me and comeing in my direction, but quickly relised 1. there is no sound. 2 . its actualy travelling away from me. the iniatal glare of it getting brighter was it powering up to shoot away at an incredible speed. i aproxmate it travelled couple of miles in less than 5 seconds. where it no was size of a small star , as it began to slow down and changed direction now moveing from right to left across my scope screen . 
i have it all recorded and have uploaded to youtube. ive tryed myself to determin what it is, but im no computer expert. at its distance , from a starting position to reach the speed it did, in my opion is imposible useing current technoligies, even jet with afterburners would have nocked me on my backside. this is not first time ive seen this object, or objects simalar, but is best in regards to video evidqnce i managed to catch it on tape. later when i was copying film from camara to laptop i  noticed 4 pictures in my camras memory , only they wernt pictures id taken or even could be taken they look like diagrams of some kind, not sure if they meen anything or even if its related . attached them to have a look, if u want to look at tape plse email me with caps in title.
content.summary: Have it on night scope, not sure how it gets so close undetected , starts as stationary aprox 200m away, then shoots into distance silently , getting brighter as it goes.
